fields.value: Projections of the Population of States by Age, Sex, and Race [United States]: 1988 to 2010

authorName.value: United States Department of Commerce. Bureau of the Census

authorAffiliation.value: United States Department of Commerce. Bureau of the Census

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This dataset provides annual population projections for the   50 states and the District of Columbia by age, sex, and race for the   years 1986 through 2010. The projections were made using a mathematical   projection model called the cohort-component method. This method allows   separate assumptions to be made for each of the components of   population change: births, deaths, internal migration, and   international migration. The projecti
ons are consistent with the July   1, 1986 population estimates for states. In general, the projections   assume a slight increase in the national levels of fertility, an   increasing level of life expectancy, and a decreasing level of net   international migration. Internal migration assumptions are based on  the annual state-to-state migration data for the years 1975-1986.
